The United States has strongly condemned the recent terrorist attacks in Afghanistan, including an attack on Parliamentary buildings in Kabul that killed at least 38 people and wounded over 70. The US also condemns a separate attack in Kandahar that killed at least seven people, including the United Arab Emirates' Ambassador to Afghanistan, as well as a suicide bomb attack in Helmand province that killed seven Afghans. The US applauds the bravery of Afghan security forces and supports their efforts to bring the perpetrators to justice. The United States reaffirms its commitment to working with the people and government of Afghanistan to create a more secure and prosperous nation.